Looking at Ukrainian electoral law, specifically the Law on Local Elections, regular elections for local councils and mayors are held on a specific date in the fifth year of their term.

According to Article 5 of the Law of Ukraine "On Local Elections," regular elections of village, settlement, city, district, and regional councils, as well as village, settlement, and city mayors, are held on the last Sunday of October of the fifth year of authority of the respective council or mayor elected in regular elections.

